{
  "topic": "Government shutdown",
  "sides": [    {
      "id": "A",
      "label": "liberal",
      "arguments": [        "Government shutdowns are reckless and harm millions of Americans by disrupting essential services, federal paychecks, and economic stability [1].",
        "Shutdowns are often used as political leverage by conservatives to force spending cuts or policy concessions, which undermines democratic negotiation and responsible governance [2].",
        "The economic cost of shutdowns far outweighs any potential savings, as they damage consumer confidence, delay government contracts, and waste taxpayer money [1].",
        "Liberals argue that funding the government is a basic responsibility of Congress, and holding it hostage for ideological demands is irresponsible [2]."
      ],
      "sources": [        "https://www.nytimes.com/2023/09/30/us/politics/government-shutdown-impacts.html",
        "https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2023/09/29/government-shutdown-republicans-democrats/"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "B",
      "label": "conservative",
      "arguments": [        "Shutdowns are sometimes necessary to force debate over runaway government spending and to demand fiscal responsibility from Congress [3].",
        "Conservatives argue that Democrats refuse to negotiate on spending cuts or border security, leaving shutdowns as the only leverage to address these issues [4].",
        "Short-term pain from a shutdown is justified if it leads to long-term reforms and prevents the government from accumulating unsustainable debt [3].",
        "Conservatives believe that the threat of a shutdown is a legitimate tool to check executive overreach and ensure that taxpayer money is spent wisely [4]."
      ],
      "sources": [        "https://www.foxnews.com/politics/government-shutdown-what-republicans-want",
        "https://www.nationalreview.com/2023/09/the-case-for-a-government-shutdown/"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
